name: Air Terjun Blemantung
address: Pujungan, Pupuan, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82163, Indonesia
review 1: The best waterfall we've been in Bali :)
review 2: Its a long hike to the waterfall but totally worth it
review 3: Amazing Waterfall, 20minute walk down from the car park, tickets about 30k. Path quite slippery, wear trainers. Totally worth the little climb down. Amazing to swim in, nice and chilly!
review 4: Keep on walking through some beautiful Cacao, Coffee, and Cloves farms, I ended up in this incredible spot! Flowing pretty freely.
review 5: Great hike through a coffee plantation ends up at the waterfall. Perfect to cool a bit on a hot day. Payed a 15000 donation ticket for restauration and maintenance purposes.

name: Waterfall Pupuan
address: Unnamed Road,, M2JV+6QG, Pujungan, Kec. Pupuan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82163, Indonesia
review 1: Best one so far, no one there as well.
review 2: Tried to find this in 2017 but there was just a wooden bridge and the locals driving by said it is a long walk that hasn't been developed yet, so you will need to find someone from the village to take you. We gave it a skip. The guide should add their contact details to this google maps listing so that people can contact then visit more easily.
review 4: Get a guide It's hard to find and it along walk down But really beautiful
